h an accuracy\nfrom $\\sigma(A_\\mathrm{V})=0.04$ to 0.15 for high and low Galactic latitudes,\nrespectively. Green et al. (2019) and Anders et al. (2022) give in unison an\nestimate of $A_\\mathrm{V}=0.12^m$ for the extinction at high latitudes across\nthe whole Galactic dust half-layer above or below the Sun with the natural\nfluctuations of the medium $\\sigma(A_\\mathrm{V})=0.06^m$. Our model is a step\nto explain how a substantial amount of dust ended up far from the Galactic\nmidplane.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2023 04:14:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-09"}
