al is d$_{x^2-y^2}$. Therefore, we believe\nthat the occupancy of out of plane oriented Cu d$_{z^2}$ orbital in place of\nplanar d$_{x^2-y^2}$ orbital along with the frustrating exchange interaction\ndrive the spins to align along $c$ in doped compound.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2023 14:21:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-09"}
